    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Hey, I'm looking over this NDA for a new client and I'm a bit stuck on the indemnification part. Can you explain what this actually means for me personally? Here is the text:\n\n\"The Recipient shall indemnify, defend, and hold harmless the Disclosing Party from and against any and all losses, damages, liabilities, deficiencies, claims, actions, judgments, settlements, interest, awards, penalties, fines, costs, or expenses of whatever kind, including reasonable attorneys' fees, arising out of or occurring in connection with any breach of this Agreement or the negligence or willful misconduct of the Recipient or its representatives.\"",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Sure, I can help with that. Indemnification in this context means that you, as the Recipient, are agreeing to protect and cover the Disclosing Party from any losses or liabilities that might arise due to you breaching this Agreement or if you or your representatives act negligently or willfully misbehave. It’s essentially a promise to hold the Disclosing Party harmless from any legal or financial consequences that result from your actions or inactions. This includes covering any legal fees and other related costs. It’s important to understand this because it means you’re taking on a significant responsibility and risk. Make sure you’re comfortable with this before you sign.",
